WEBVTT

00:02.470 --> 00:05.166
***

00:09.810 --> 00:11.766
- Ha ha ha! Five in a row.
Drink up.

00:11.810 --> 00:15.632
- Why does the
loser have to drink?
- Guess who just landed

00:15.680 --> 00:18.706
a new client?
We are made in the Shade,

00:18.750 --> 00:20.809
and yes, I just said that.

00:20.850 --> 00:25.139
Wow. Is this as strangely
provocative as it looks?

00:25.190 --> 00:27.454
Maybe don't answer.
- We're celebrating!

00:27.490 --> 00:29.458
Maz is getting promoted
to Detective Sergeant.

00:29.490 --> 00:32.596
It's not official yet.

00:32.630 --> 00:35.121
- Come on, even I heard
the rumour. You're a lock.

00:35.160 --> 00:38.163
- Congrats, but can we bring
it back to me for a second?
My Craigslist ad paid off.

00:38.200 --> 00:41.135
Solid plan.

00:41.170 --> 00:43.809
- This one is the real deal.
The guy's name is Jay Lee.

00:43.840 --> 00:45.808
He owns an awesome
karaoke bar and he makes

00:45.840 --> 00:49.071
the best absinthe flip
you've ever tasted.

00:49.110 --> 00:51.442
- Intriguing. Put the file on
my desk. I'll look at it later.

00:51.480 --> 00:54.313
- Yeah, here's the thing:
I kinda said yes.

00:54.350 --> 00:57.080
- Oh, dude, you should have
vetted it through Angie.

00:57.120 --> 00:59.418
There's a lot of nutbars
on the interweb.

01:02.860 --> 01:06.227
- * Born to be wild

01:09.470 --> 01:11.620
* Born to be wild

01:11.670 --> 01:13.638
- Hey, we're looking
for Jay Lee?

01:13.670 --> 01:16.366
- Out back.
- Thanks.

01:16.410 --> 01:18.628
- Hell, no. Shades don't sing.

01:18.670 --> 01:20.706
At least not in public.

01:20.740 --> 01:22.844
- Huh. I thought your hockey
career made you impervious

01:22.880 --> 01:25.178
to public humiliation.
- My hockey paycheques

01:25.210 --> 01:27.314
made me impervious
to public humiliation.

01:27.350 --> 01:30.217
There's our client.

01:30.250 --> 01:32.718
Look, I know you're all about
researching our clients

01:32.760 --> 01:34.853
before you commit,
but Jay is genuinely scared.

01:34.890 --> 01:38.849
- He thinks he's being followed.

01:38.890 --> 01:40.790
He wants us to watch him
day and night. You know,

01:40.830 --> 01:43.719
snap some pictures, keep an eye
out for suspicious characters.

01:46.700 --> 01:48.668
- I'm gonna need more specifics.

01:48.700 --> 01:51.737
- A friend of his suddenly went
missing and it's got him
kind of freaked out.

01:51.770 --> 01:53.874
- Guy's name is Teddy Sparkle.

01:53.910 --> 01:56.777
- Did Teddy Sparkle disappear
with or without his unicorn?

01:56.810 --> 01:59.677
- You mock because you didn't
bring this case in yourself.

01:59.720 --> 02:02.143
- Well, I'd prefer
if you'd asked me first.

02:02.190 --> 02:05.910
I mean, I have more experience
vetting the marginal customers.

02:05.950 --> 02:08.282
- This isn't that kind of case.
Jay's a stand-up guy.

02:14.660 --> 02:16.525
- If by stand-up guy
you mean drug dealer...

02:18.600 --> 02:20.795
Give your buddy his money back.
I'm calling this one.

02:22.970 --> 02:25.268
- Wait! Do you remember
why you first hired me?

02:25.310 --> 02:27.437
- Good instincts.

02:27.480 --> 02:29.505
My gut tells me there's
something here, Angie.

02:29.550 --> 02:31.939
Do you trust me or not?

02:31.980 --> 02:35.814
- This better be one
amazing absinthe flip.

02:38.820 --> 02:42.654
***

02:42.690 --> 02:45.523
- I know how it looked,
but it's not what you think.

02:45.560 --> 02:48.290
I'm not a dealer.

02:48.330 --> 02:50.469
- I'm not really
at liberty to say.

02:50.500 --> 02:53.264
All I can tell you is nice
catch. You guys are clearly

02:53.300 --> 02:55.860
the right people for the job,
and please keep it up.

02:55.900 --> 02:58.937
- Is this part of some
elaborate hipster art project?

02:58.970 --> 03:01.939
Are we going to be on Vimeo?
- I'm pretty sure

03:01.980 --> 03:04.403
I'm in danger.

03:04.450 --> 03:06.418
It's hard to explain.
- Well, give it a shot.

03:06.450 --> 03:08.418
Tell us about your
friend who disappeared,

03:08.450 --> 03:11.317
Teddy Not-His-Real-Name Sparkle.
- Teddy and I met here.

03:11.350 --> 03:14.285
He was a regular
at 305 Jazz Night.

03:14.320 --> 03:16.982
A while back, he got busted
with an ounce of weed

03:17.030 --> 03:20.488
and he... he changed.

03:20.530 --> 03:22.964
Got paranoid, wouldn't
talk about it and then...

03:23.000 --> 03:25.468
I haven't seen him
for two weeks.

03:25.500 --> 03:27.559
- And you think the same thing's
gonna happen to you?

03:27.600 --> 03:30.501
- We hang in the same circles.
- Drug-dealing circles.

03:30.540 --> 03:32.906
- I swear I don't sell drugs.

03:32.940 --> 03:35.875
But I feel this malevolent
presence around me.

03:35.910 --> 03:38.777
If you guys tail me,
keep an eye out, maybe we can,

03:38.810 --> 03:42.348
you can find out who.
But don't come too c-close.

03:42.390 --> 03:44.244
You cannot,
under any circumstances,

03:44.290 --> 03:46.258
get caught tailing me.

03:46.290 --> 03:48.315
And it's only for two days.
If you still think I'm crooked

03:48.360 --> 03:50.328
after that, call the c-c-cops.

03:50.360 --> 03:52.999
No, no, no,
just scratch that. Uh...

03:53.030 --> 03:55.999
Please. I need your help.

03:56.030 --> 03:59.796
- Look, I have no illusions
about why people come to P.I.s

03:59.840 --> 04:02.400
and I'm not big on judging.

04:02.440 --> 04:05.466
But I don't work for dealers.

04:05.510 --> 04:09.276
Two days. And we'll walk sooner
if you're shining us on.

04:13.520 --> 04:16.045
- Look, just between me
and you, what's going on?

04:16.080 --> 04:18.742
You're making me look bad.
- Sorry, Shade.

04:18.790 --> 04:21.816
I never want to make a man look
less than amazmg In front
of his woman.

04:21.860 --> 04:24.055
- Angie's my boss!

04:24.090 --> 04:27.753
- I am not getting boss vibes.

04:35.540 --> 04:39.032
- ** I see you and you see me

