* Watching you *

05:10.710 --> 05:12.928
***

05:12.980 --> 05:15.107
- Scrambled eggs, pea meal
bacon. Jules's favourite,

05:15.140 --> 05:17.938
always has been.
- If she's late getting up,

05:17.980 --> 05:21.017
she doesn't get her vote.
Over-easy, sausage.

05:21.050 --> 05:23.541
- This is your granddaughter
we're talking about here.

05:23.590 --> 05:25.581
- Game on.

05:30.730 --> 05:33.358
- Jules, your grandfather's
trying to cheat us

05:33.400 --> 05:36.722
out of scrambled eggs, again.
- OK, anything but eggs.

05:36.770 --> 05:38.863
Ariel snuck tamagoyaki
into the play last night

05:38.900 --> 05:40.868
and I am done with eggs
for a week.

05:40.900 --> 05:44.563
- Granola it is.

05:44.610 --> 05:46.498
- Only the coolest
girl in drama.

05:46.540 --> 05:48.701
- Look at you, hitting it off
with the cool kids.

05:48.740 --> 05:51.777
- Yeah, and they're seniors.
Can't believe they invited me.

05:51.810 --> 05:54.779
But I'm probably never going
to hear from them again.

05:54.820 --> 05:57.789
- So call them. D_oesn't hurt
to prove you're Interested.

05:57.820 --> 05:59.879
- No, no.

05:59.920 --> 06:02.627
In this scenario, if you want
to be the cool kid, you gotta

06:02.660 --> 06:04.457
hang back. Let them reach out.
- Me and Ariel are hitting

06:04.490 --> 06:06.458
the mall after school.
- It's only a matter of time

06:06.500 --> 06:08.991
before they call you.
- Sorry, I wasn't listening.

06:09.030 --> 06:12.466
Gotta get back to her.

06:12.500 --> 06:15.799
- My coolest father moment ever,
and she didn't even notice.

06:15.840 --> 06:18.832
- Yep. Get used to it.

06:21.910 --> 06:24.071
- Sparkle. Uh, Teddy,
or Theodore?

06:24.110 --> 06:26.670
See if he's shown up
as a missing person.

06:26.720 --> 06:28.938
OK. Thanks, Maz.

06:28.980 --> 06:32.484
- Maz again. You guys
really are close.

06:32.520 --> 06:34.886
- Well, I'm happy to call him
a friend. I'll be very happy

06:34.920 --> 06:36.888
to call him Detective Sergeant.
- Good to have friends

06:36.930 --> 06:38.886
in high places.
- Clients in high places,

06:38.930 --> 06:41.649
however...
- He's doing ﬁne.

06:41.700 --> 06:44.919
His bar is thriving, even
if he is an MBA drop-out

06:44.970 --> 06:48.758
with a bachelor's degree in...
philosophy and botany?

06:48.800 --> 06:50.961
- Perfect for a bartender.
I spoke to a loose-lipped

06:51.010 --> 06:53.706
teller at his bank. He hasn't
missed a smgle loan payment.

06:53.740 --> 06:55.776
- Told you. He's a good kid.

06:55.810 --> 06:58.677
- I wonder if the mob's
trying to shake him down.

06:58.710 --> 07:02.544
His bar is in their wheelhouse.
- Are you warmIng up to our
botany

07:02.590 --> 07:05.047
- Like you said: paid in cash.

07:05.090 --> 07:07.809
Plus, he does have
an interesting tell.

07:07.860 --> 07:10.226
- Do tell.
- Well, he's got a...

07:10.260 --> 07:12.558
he's got a stutter that comes
out every one in a while.

07:12.600 --> 07:15.160
I'm not sure what triggers it,
but it's there.

07:17.270 --> 07:20.535
***

07:20.570 --> 07:23.130
He's really ticking off
all the hipster boxes.

07:23.170 --> 07:25.604
Is he going to pick up
some beard oil next?

07:25.640 --> 07:29.076
- He doesn't have a beard. And
why are you so hard on hipsters?

07:29.110 --> 07:31.601
- They claim to defile trends,
but they're all about image.

07:31.650 --> 07:33.948
Take his bike,
that ridiculous cart.

07:33.980 --> 07:35.948
It screams,
"Look how unique I am!"

07:35.980 --> 07:37.743
Or that he lost his oxen.

07:37.790 --> 07:40.953
- I think hipsters get a bad
rap. Once you get past

07:40.990 --> 07:43.959
the tattoos and the skinny
jeans, you have to admit,
they make a mean coffee.

07:43.990 --> 07:45.958
- Which they aren't afraid
to let you know about.

07:45.990 --> 07:48.959
- Think of all the good things
that've come out of the
hipster movement...

07:49.000 --> 07:51.696
Artisanal cheese: good.
Craft beers: good.

07:51.730 --> 07:55.860
- Amish hats, oversized glasses,
man buns: less good.

07:55.900 --> 07:58.562
- Yeah. Point well taken. Oh!

07:58.610 --> 08:02.876
Hipster on the move.

08:05.310 --> 08:08.108
- Hey, slow down, partner.
- Hey, babe. Nice to hear

08:08.150 --> 08:10.983
your voice, but I'd prefer to
k-keep this a long-distance
relationship.

08:11.020 --> 08:13.989
- Hey, dude, I like you too, but
let's ease up on the intimacy.

08:14.020 --> 08:17.057
- Better if you don't call me,
babe, 'K? I need my space.

08:19.030 --> 08:22.056
- I thought the artisanal
marijuana skipped the
paranoia factor.

08:22.100 --> 08:23.988
- There was that stutter
you were talking about.

08:24.030 --> 08:25.998
- OK, I'm only half-joking
about the paranoia thing.

08:26.030 --> 08:27.998
We have to consider that
Jay might be out of his tree.

08:28.040 --> 08:29.905
- We also have to consider
he has a reason to be speaking

08:29.940 --> 08:32.738
in code. Maybe his
pursuers are here.

08:32.780 --> 08:34.805
- The only people
stalking him are us.

08:34.840 --> 08:37.547
- Houston, we have a box.

08:41.120 --> 08:43.088
- I can't... I can't get him.
His back's to us.

08:43.120 --> 08:45.748
- Call me in 20 seconds.

08:45.790 --> 08:48.156
- Shade!
: Do we have enough time?

08:48.190 --> 08:50.658
This is it.

08:50.690 --> 08:53.955
Oh, hey, honey.

08:54.000 --> 08:55.922
- Yeah, yeah, sure.

08:55.960 --> 09:00.033
Two bottles? Yeah. Yeah, sure,
I'll stop by the liquor store.

09:00.070 --> 09:03.039
Women, right?

09:09.950 --> 09:12.976
It was nothing. He was buying
a vintage board game.

09:13.020 --> 09:15.978
- I'm just saying it was
reckless. Seems to be an ongoing

09:16.020 --> 09:17.988
theme with you these days.
- Did I or did I not

09:18.020 --> 09:21.114
get the photo?
- So far we've confirmed

09:21.160 --> 09:24.584
your client enjoys obscure
vinyl, Truth Apocalypse

09:24.630 --> 09:27.349
and now he's buying rutabagas.
- Just give it some time.

09:27.400 --> 09:30.267
- If it's any consolation,

09:30.300 --> 09:32.325
I think he's telling
the truth about last night.

09:32.370 --> 09:34.361
Everything about
his business seems legit.

09:34.400 --> 09:36.937
Twee as hell, but legit.

09:36.970 --> 09:39.973
- Well, maybe he makes more
money than he's letting
on and he's hiding it.

09:40.010 --> 09:43.741
- Well, if the mob shows up,
you'll have to ask them.

09:43.780 --> 09:45.805
- I have a summons to pop off

09:45.850 --> 09:48.216
and a mound of paperwork. You
can handle gamer boy from here.

09:48.250 --> 09:51.014
- Most dangerous thing he's done

09:51.050 --> 09:53.086
is fondle some organic fruit.

09:53.120 --> 09:55.111
I think you can
take it from here.

10:00.160 --> 10:02.151
- OK...

10:15.910 --> 10:18.708
Jay, what's up?

10:18.750 --> 10:22.049
I know I asked you to distance
yourself, but I feel like

10:22.080 --> 10:24.048
- I'm right here!

10:24.090 --> 10:27.059
- Uh, I feel like I want
you to be c-c-close.

10:27.090 --> 10:29.854
- I'm coming to you.

10:29.890 --> 10:32.927
I was wrong. You
and me, we're not working out.]

10:32.960 --> 10:35.019
Don't c-c-call me again.

10:38.300 --> 10:41.098
I'm sorry about that.
: Come on!

10:45.170 --> 10:48.071
- Alright, peace out.
I'll see you later, alright?

