***

10:58.190 --> 11:00.010
- Whoa! Sorry.

11:00.060 --> 11:03.848
Just got, uh...

11:08.200 --> 11:10.691
- Wait, don't... shake...

11:12.940 --> 11:15.431
I
You lied to me, man.

11:23.880 --> 11:26.075
Stay here.

11:45.100 --> 11:47.364
I screwed up.
- Hold on! Wait.

11:47.400 --> 11:49.800
I've got popcorn here somewhere.

11:49.840 --> 11:51.808
- Jay's a dealer. I should have
vetted this through you.

11:51.840 --> 11:54.206
I'm sorry.
- With a kilo of coke.

11:54.240 --> 11:56.947
And what's a board-
game—playing hipster

11:56.980 --> 11:59.005
doing with a semi
- I don't know!

11:59.050 --> 12:02.816
It's for crowd control at
a Settlers of Cattan marathon?

12:02.850 --> 12:06.081
Jay's a liar. You called it.
- I checked into Jay's
missing buddy.

12:06.120 --> 12:08.111
Teddy Sparkle's entire
social media footprint

12:08.160 --> 12:11.823
went dark two weeks ago.
- His so-called buddy's
probably not even real.

12:11.860 --> 12:14.351
- Then how do you explain
Jay's behaviour?

12:14.400 --> 12:16.254
- I don't know! He's a dealer!
The mob's probably after him

12:16.300 --> 12:19.292
for cutting in on their turf.
- Mobsters don't play
board games.

12:19.330 --> 12:23.164
Everett Investigations.

12:23.210 --> 12:25.269
- Angie, it's Jules. If you're
with my dad right now,

12:25.310 --> 12:27.278
don't say anything. Please.

12:30.480 --> 12:33.040
- I need your help.
I'm in trouble.

12:33.080 --> 12:36.846
- It's a possible
adultery case. Uh...

12:36.890 --> 12:40.155
Care to talk about it?
- I'm at the police station.

12:40.190 --> 12:42.408
57 Division.
- OK.

12:42.460 --> 12:45.258
I will come to you, then.

12:45.290 --> 12:47.451
- Oh, God.

12:47.500 --> 12:50.128
I hope not, but I have to go.

12:50.170 --> 12:53.537
You were right when you said
I hired you for your instincts.

12:53.570 --> 12:56.289
Don't give up on them now.

13:06.380 --> 13:09.144
Thanks, I'll take it from here.

13:09.180 --> 13:11.842
Hey, Jules.

13:14.960 --> 13:17.224
So?

13:19.460 --> 13:21.894
I was at the mall
with my friends

13:21.930 --> 13:24.160
and they're older than me
and I don't even know

13:24.200 --> 13:26.168
why they want me around.

13:26.200 --> 13:29.829
So I told them,
"Hey! Hey, watch this.

13:29.870 --> 13:33.203
No one ever suspects
the blind girl."

13:33.240 --> 13:35.504
And I stole something.

13:38.350 --> 13:41.239
- The manager suspected
the blind girl.

13:41.280 --> 13:43.316
: You get
anything good?

13:43.350 --> 13:46.547
- A t-shirt. Didn't even
get the right Size.

13:48.490 --> 13:51.152
- Hey. Did I ever tell you
about the time I got busted?

13:56.160 --> 13:58.060
You have no idea how much
time I had to waste

13:58.100 --> 14:00.489
proving that I wasn't a narc,
which means that I shoplifted

14:00.540 --> 14:03.862
my fanny off.
Mascara, chocolate, a bra...

14:06.510 --> 14:08.535
- Look, I know.

14:08.580 --> 14:10.571
I know I have to tell my dad.

14:13.520 --> 14:16.216
But I just want to figure out
how to do it, you know?

14:16.250 --> 14:19.117
- Oh, crap! Your dad's here.

14:22.260 --> 14:25.149
- The chamomile--
- Congrats!

14:25.190 --> 14:28.250
Hi! Hey, don't jinx it, OK?
It hasn't happened yet.

14:33.070 --> 14:35.129
- Hey, do you know when
Mazhari's getting back?

14:39.210 --> 14:43.101
- If this is about girl guide
cookies, I'll take a box.

14:43.150 --> 14:46.005
- Hey, Mazhari. Do you
know who this guy is?

14:46.050 --> 14:48.109
- Holy crap. Edgar Brava.
What are you messing

14:48.150 --> 14:50.118
with a guy like that for?

14:50.150 --> 14:53.381
- He's a new breed of bad guy.
He's a fake community booster

14:53.420 --> 14:56.253
who deals hard drugs to the
west end. It's a shame he's such

14:56.290 --> 14:58.258
a dick, though, 'cause I saw him
at Mariposa's one night.

14:58.290 --> 15:00.155
Man is a world-class
salsa dancer.

15:00.200 --> 15:02.395
- Tell me more
about your man crush.

15:02.430 --> 15:04.523
- Hey, I am comfortable
enough in my masculinity

15:04.570 --> 15:07.130
to admire another
man's Paso La Jenny.

15:07.170 --> 15:09.297
Edgar works for one of the bigs.

15:12.170 --> 15:15.071
Man by the name of Simon Tyrell.
Drug squad's been after him
for years.

15:15.110 --> 15:17.999
Now, Tyrell runs his business
like a legitimate operation --

15:18.050 --> 15:21.178
health benefits, two weeks paid
vacation -- but you screw up,

15:21.220 --> 15:25.281
your retirement plan starts
immediately and six feet under.

15:25.320 --> 15:27.288
- So what, you're Little Shade's
emergency contact?

15:27.320 --> 15:30.221
- Hardly. I don't know how
she got my phone number.

15:30.260 --> 15:32.148
- And now here you are, busting
her out of shoplifting jail.

15:32.190 --> 15:34.158
- That's what partners do.
- Aw, look at you

15:34.200 --> 15:36.156
and your soft spot.
- I don't have any soft spots.

15:36.200 --> 15:41.092
- Actually, if my memory
serves me correctly...

15:41.140 --> 15:43.199
- She's... she's right there.

15:47.210 --> 15:51.044
- Hey, kid.
Careful you don't go--

15:51.080 --> 15:53.173
At this point,

15:53.220 --> 15:55.347
I might as well go for
the full-on Helen Keller.

15:55.380 --> 15:57.245
- OK. I think it's about time

15:57.290 --> 16:00.009
the two of you stopped
hiding out in my office.

16:02.220 --> 16:04.529
- Shade's still here!

16:07.260 --> 16:10.195
- Sometimes I think he just
slams it for the attention.

16:10.230 --> 16:13.097
- It's a case of ours.

16:13.140 --> 16:15.335
I thought it was a pass,
but our client has a friend

16:15.370 --> 16:17.338
who's gone missing and
now he's afraid he's next.

16:19.370 --> 16:22.203
I asked Maz to
check on it for me.

16:22.240 --> 16:26.540
- Teddy Sparkle is a kid
named Teddy Borges.

16:26.580 --> 16:29.117
And Teddy Borges is dead.

16:31.290 --> 16:33.281
- Mm-hmm.

16:33.320 --> 16:35.254
- So, Edgar Bravas.
Is he as dangerous as his boss?

16:35.290 --> 16:37.429
- Mm. Don't let the
baby-face fool you.

16:37.460 --> 16:39.758
He did five years on his last
stretch. The guy is scum.

16:39.790 --> 16:42.520
Excuse me.

16:42.560 --> 16:45.222
Mazhari?

16:45.270 --> 16:47.397
Angie, hey!

16:47.440 --> 16:49.499
Yeah, I had a really good time,
too. You owe me a rematch,

16:49.540 --> 16:52.361
young lady.
- I totally won fair and square.

16:52.410 --> 16:55.379
I'm on the phone
with somebody over here.
- Give me the phone.

16:55.410 --> 16:58.243
- Yeah, your partner's in the
office. He's got into some
real serious sh--

16:58.280 --> 17:00.248
Yeah, I might
have found something

17:00.280 --> 17:02.544
that's real trouble. Yeah, OK.

17:02.580 --> 17:04.810
Yeah, I'll meet you
back at the agency.

17:04.850 --> 17:07.216
Still think I needed
to vet this through Angie?

17:09.320 --> 17:11.356
***

17:15.560 --> 17:18.290
You were right.
About me being right.

17:18.330 --> 17:20.264
Meet Edgar Brava,

17:20.300 --> 17:22.336
the man who dropped
the drugs in Jay's buggy.

17:22.370 --> 17:24.463
Spent six years in prison
on a half-dozen charges,

17:24.510 --> 17:27.206
all drugs and guns related.
Jay's a pothead.

17:27.240 --> 17:29.800
Nothing about him adds up
to being besties with this guy.

17:29.840 --> 17:34.072
- This is Teddy Borges,
Jay's friend.

17:34.120 --> 17:36.076
He died two weeks ago.
Two shots to the head.

17:36.120 --> 17:38.816
The case landed on Nolan's desk.
What I learned about Teddy

17:38.850 --> 17:41.853
doesn't add up to Edgar Brava
either. He worked three jobs,

17:41.890 --> 17:44.154
did a lot of yoga,
smoked a lot of weed.

17:44.190 --> 17:45.748
- Do the police have any
suspects in his murder?

17:45.790 --> 17:48.588
- Drug-related is all
Nolan would say.

17:48.630 --> 17:50.564
- So, two hipsters.

17:50.600 --> 17:53.433
One dead, one convinced
he's about to be.

17:53.470 --> 17:56.189
- Both caught up in dealing,
but neither fitting the profile

17:56.240 --> 17:58.231
of a criminal.
- When I was tailing Jay,

17:58.270 --> 18:00.238
he started up with the
sweetheart talk again,

18:00.280 --> 18:02.236
until Edgar Brava
pulled up next to him.

18:02.280 --> 18:05.443
- So they talked and then Brava
put the drugs in his cart.

18:05.480 --> 18:07.710
- That's right.
He was also stuttering.

18:07.750 --> 18:10.389
- Which he does when
he's scared, especially...

18:10.420 --> 18:12.718
when we mention police. Shade!

18:12.750 --> 18:14.718
Maybe Jay's a CI.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.751
- Confidential informant.

18:16.790 --> 18:18.758
Let's say the cops
bust Jay for possession.

18:18.790 --> 18:20.849
A possession charge would
threaten Jay's business,

18:20.900 --> 18:22.856
so the cop convinces
him to wear a wire

18:22.900 --> 18:25.596
and take down some bad guys.
- So he snitches for the cops

18:25.630 --> 18:28.497
to reduce the charges. If he's
a C.I., why not just tell us?

18:28.540 --> 18:31.338
- Because all C.I.s sign
confidentiality contracts.

18:31.370 --> 18:33.907
If he breaks it, he goes to jail
on the original drug charges

18:33.940 --> 18:35.908
and on new ones for
breaking the contract.

18:35.940 --> 18:38.249
- So he's trying to show us
what he is without telling us.

18:38.280 --> 18:40.248
And all that girlfriend
talk on the phone--

18:40.280 --> 18:42.510
- Is because he's wearing a wire
when he makes the buys!

18:42.550 --> 18:44.609
- And I almost blew his cover.

18:44.650 --> 18:47.756
- This kid's afraid for
his life... with good reason.

18:51.190 --> 18:53.192
(song: Danny Boy
by Frederic Weatherly)

18:55.660 --> 18:57.924
- Private event!
- Hey, buddy.

18:57.970 --> 19:01.235
I decided not to take
being dumped personally.

19:01.270 --> 19:03.261
- Uh, like I said, mister...

19:03.310 --> 19:05.266
...private event.

19:05.310 --> 19:08.529
- Well, hey, man.

19:08.580 --> 19:11.299
Sure. Uh, peace out.

19:22.560 --> 19:25.427
: Go! Go, go, go!
: Which way?

19:25.460 --> 19:27.257
- Get out of my way!

19:31.970 --> 19:34.939
- Ow!

19:38.010 --> 19:40.729
Hey, hey. Uh, sorry.

19:40.780 --> 19:42.736
- Hey, don't apologize
for loving to sing, Jay.

19:42.780 --> 19:44.748
- Just don't sing
to the wrong people.

19:44.780 --> 19:48.238
- Of course, Mr. Tyrell. Please.

19:55.460 --> 20:00.227
So, uh, Edgar says we c-can
move our relationship forward.

20:00.260 --> 20:02.728
- Edgar tells me you want
liquid cocaine.

20:02.760 --> 20:05.320
Pretty ambitious, Mr. Lee.

20:05.370 --> 20:07.361
Cutting edge.

20:07.400 --> 20:09.561
- Yeah, well, you can take
the kid out of MBA school

20:09.600 --> 20:12.728
but you can't take an interest
in profit differentials
out of the kid.

20:12.770 --> 20:17.707
- Yeah, I'm an MBA as well.
Let me guess, Keynesian?

20:17.750 --> 20:20.378
- More of a Hayek man myself.

20:20.420 --> 20:22.877
- I like you.

20:22.920 --> 20:24.911
We'll do this.

20:27.360 --> 20:29.612
But not here.

20:29.660 --> 20:32.379
- But I thought you wanted--
- Mr. Tyrell said no.

20:34.400 --> 20:36.459
Mr. Tyrell?

20:41.070 --> 20:43.402
- His handler must be close.
- You check out front.

20:43.440 --> 20:45.431
I'll take the back.

20:55.320 --> 20:57.743
- Hey.
- 'K, I got him.

20:57.790 --> 20:59.644
His handler's here.
I'm going in for a closer look.

20:59.690 --> 21:02.352
- No! No. If they spot you,
it's game over for Jay.

21:02.390 --> 21:04.529
- He may take it out on him
anyway. The deal didn't happen.

21:06.330 --> 21:09.629
OK, he's getting out.

21:09.660 --> 21:11.924
- Stay put.

21:11.970 --> 21:14.438
- He's driving away.

21:14.470 --> 21:16.961
We lost him.

21:19.070 --> 21:22.801
- Woo!

21:22.840 --> 21:24.671
Sorry.

21:28.080 --> 21:31.686
- Wow. My boss is amazing.

21:31.720 --> 21:36.316
- We believe you signed a
confidential informant contract.

21:36.360 --> 21:38.328
- You've got a stutter
that comes out sometimes,

21:38.360 --> 21:40.590
we think whenever you're wearing
a wire, and you talk to us

21:40.630 --> 21:43.394
in code when we're following
you, which is pretty smart.

21:43.430 --> 21:46.661
- And you're afraid to talk
about it because you think
you'll go to jail.

21:46.700 --> 21:48.861
- Can't believe
you don't have Angostura.

21:48.900 --> 21:51.107
Everybody has Angostura.
- We're pretty sure

21:51.140 --> 21:53.108
you're not wired now,
or else you wouldn't be here.

21:53.140 --> 21:56.109
Are we close?
- Any cop that would put you
in that situation is working

21:56.140 --> 21:59.405
way outside the law
and needs to be stopped.

21:59.450 --> 22:02.840
I saw his face. All we need
from you is a name. Who is he?

22:06.120 --> 22:10.079
- I am so sorry for getting
you guys into this.

22:10.120 --> 22:12.429
I gotta go.

22:12.460 --> 22:14.758
- Teddy's dead.

22:14.800 --> 22:18.827
- He was murdered. Shot twice
In the head, execution style.

22:18.870 --> 22:22.431
The police think it was
a drug deal gone sideways.

22:22.470 --> 22:24.028
- We think he was
a CI. just like you.

22:24.070 --> 22:26.630
He died alone, feeling
like he was trapped

22:26.670 --> 22:28.604
in an impossible situation.

22:28.640 --> 22:30.642
- You're not alone here, Jay.

22:34.750 --> 22:37.014
- I keep thinking,
this is the last one.

22:37.050 --> 22:39.848
I'll make one more deal,

22:39.890 --> 22:42.358
then it'll be the last one.

22:44.190 --> 22:46.522
But it never stops.

22:46.560 --> 22:49.654
- We can stop it.

22:49.700 --> 22:52.692
- We just need his name.

22:57.040 --> 22:59.031
_ [There's no Nick Bradley
on the police force.]

22:59.070 --> 23:02.938
- That's not possible.
- Maybe Jay's handler
is using a cover name.

23:02.980 --> 23:05.039
- That doesn't sound legit.
- If they want to stay off-book

23:05.080 --> 23:07.412
it does. We need to see Maz.

23:07.450 --> 23:09.475
- Alright, first thing
in the am. Later.

23:13.790 --> 23:17.089
What's going on?

23:17.120 --> 23:19.680
- I did something
really stupid today.

23:26.570 --> 23:29.562
So, um...

23:29.600 --> 23:31.659
My friends and I,

23:31.710 --> 23:35.168
we were in a clothing
store and...

23:35.210 --> 23:38.509
I got caught with some stuff
that I didn't pay for.

23:38.550 --> 23:40.916
- You're kidding me.

23:40.950 --> 23:42.941
- Look, my friends, they...

23:42.980 --> 23:45.187
they took some sweaters
and they dropped it in my bag

23:45.220 --> 23:47.688
and I was too afraid
to say anything.

23:47.720 --> 23:49.984
- Some friends.
- Were these friends Ariel

23:50.020 --> 23:52.659
and Cianna? 'Cause their parents
are getting a phone call right--

23:52.690 --> 23:54.829
- No, Dad, please don't.

23:54.860 --> 23:58.193
OK? I just want to forget
that today ever happened.

23:58.230 --> 24:00.221
- No, honey, you can't
just forget it!

24:00.270 --> 24:03.660
They need to know that they made
a big mistake when they took
advantage of you.

24:03.710 --> 24:06.133
- You know, Matt...

24:06.170 --> 24:08.934
I used to get all
riled at your coaches.

24:08.980 --> 24:11.141
I'd be halfway
down the driveway,

24:11.180 --> 24:13.671
plans for mayhem in my head,

24:13.720 --> 24:17.781
until I realized the impact
my actions had on you.

24:19.790 --> 24:21.985
- Alright. We can put
a pin in this...

24:22.020 --> 24:24.022
for now.

24:26.990 --> 24:30.619
I think I know what'll make you
feel better, honey. You want
some roclq road ice cream?

24:30.670 --> 24:32.968
- Um...

24:33.000 --> 24:35.935
Thanks, Dad, but I don't really
have an appetite right now.

24:42.140 --> 24:46.042
- It's not like Jules
to turn down ice cream.

24:46.080 --> 24:48.776
***

24:48.820 --> 24:52.119
- Bringing a drug dealer
in off the street

24:52.150 --> 24:54.118
is not considered
a felony, Angie.

24:54.160 --> 24:56.116
Obstructing an active police
investigation, however--

24:56.160 --> 24:58.253
- Just run Jay's profile.
- I did. He's not in the system.

24:58.290 --> 25:00.622
You're chasing your own tail.
- We know Jay's a CI.

25:00.660 --> 25:03.128
If he's not in the system, then
some rogue cop's running him

25:03.160 --> 25:05.264
off-book, and that is a felony.

25:05.300 --> 25:07.996
- He gave a false name.
Hence the off-book part.

25:08.040 --> 25:10.190
- Wow.
- I know yours

25:10.240 --> 25:12.128
is an impossible job,
but this cop has a body count.

25:12.170 --> 25:15.003
It could get worse. It stinks,
Kurtis, you know it does.

25:15.040 --> 25:17.270
- All I know is you guys have
the Karaoke Kid as a client,

25:17.310 --> 25:19.278
and you're the one
inhaling the fumes.

25:19.310 --> 25:22.211
- Wait. Your salsa-dancing,
drug-dealing man crush,

25:22.250 --> 25:24.616
Edgar Brava. Who else
likes his chubby cheeks?

25:24.650 --> 25:28.279
- Pretty much everyone.
The Four Horsemen in particular.

25:28.320 --> 25:30.925
- The Drug Squad dream team.

25:34.260 --> 25:36.148
- That's him.
That's the guy I saw, Maz.

25:36.200 --> 25:38.065
- You don't.

25:38.100 --> 25:40.295
There's untouchable and
then there's Tyler Pryce.

25:40.330 --> 25:43.902
- But I saw him.
If he's running a rogue
operation, if kids are dying--

25:43.940 --> 25:47.159
- Tyler Pryce is a legend.
He's nailed more bad
guys than Batman.

25:47.210 --> 25:50.839
- Teddy Borges was not a bad guy
and Teddy Borges is dead.

25:50.880 --> 25:53.041
I don't want Jay to be next.

25:53.080 --> 25:56.174
- You are going on
the paranoid ramblings
of a half-baked hipster.

25:56.220 --> 25:58.188
- We're going on more than that.
We saw what Jay was buying.

25:58.220 --> 26:00.950
We saw him turn
it over to Pryce.

26:03.860 --> 26:06.829
- Angie, I would do anything
for you, but I can't
touch this thing.

26:06.860 --> 26:08.851
- If this was a police
operation, wouldn't there be

26:08.900 --> 26:11.664
some kind of evidence?
- Evidence. Shade's right.

26:11.700 --> 26:13.930
Jay bought cocaine
and a handgun,

26:13.970 --> 26:15.938
which he turned over to Pryce.
So if it's on the book,

26:15.970 --> 26:18.006
it's in the records.
Call Evidence.

26:18.040 --> 26:20.258
- And what do I tell Evidence
that I'm looking for?

26:20.310 --> 26:24.679
Cops don't look into other cops,
Angie. You of all people
should know that.

26:24.710 --> 26:27.975
- You're a good cop, Maz.
Enjoy that promotion.

26:35.990 --> 26:38.959
- I'm sorry, buddy, but we're
running out of options.

26:38.990 --> 26:42.255
- A lavwer can help. Just tell
them everything you told us.

26:42.300 --> 26:45.292
- Pryce said no lawyers
or the charges stick.

26:47.300 --> 26:49.268
There's gotta be something.

26:49.300 --> 26:51.268
- Unless we can
get a cop on5ide,

26:51.310 --> 26:53.631
there's not really
much we can do.

26:53.680 --> 26:55.830
- Alright, listen. There's only

26:55.880 --> 26:57.905
one way to do this thing.
If we take down Pryce,

26:57.950 --> 27:00.305
then we, the cops, could lose
a chance to take down Tyrell,

27:00.350 --> 27:02.375
and Tyrell is scum.
- Oh, it's OK.

27:02.420 --> 27:04.285
Maz, this is Jay.

27:04.320 --> 27:06.788
Detective Mazhari.

27:06.820 --> 27:08.981
- No. You're in.

27:09.020 --> 27:11.386
- I love this man right now. If
you're not having sex with him,

27:11.430 --> 27:14.251
then I will.
- I'm regretting this already.

27:14.300 --> 27:17.861
Or whatever his name is?
- Tyler Pryce.

27:17.900 --> 27:19.720
And yeah, we're going after him.

27:19.770 --> 27:22.261
- Pryce is not the kind of man

27:22.300 --> 27:25.007
to let a loose end dangle.

27:25.040 --> 27:28.077
- Then what say
you make me the knot?

27:34.950 --> 27:38.738
- Just play it cool and
remember to breathe, alright?

27:38.790 --> 27:42.282
Out of the way, come on.
- Seriously, man, I'm not
a flight risk.

27:42.320 --> 27:44.322
- I'd say you're flying
pretty high already, punk.

27:51.330 --> 27:54.231
Hey, Pryce.

27:54.270 --> 27:57.364
Can I help you with something?

27:57.400 --> 27:59.800
Didn't know you had to make
bottom-feeder quota.

27:59.840 --> 28:02.377
- This kid just lit up
right in front of me.

28:02.410 --> 28:04.970
- Look, I know this punk.
Let me have a go.

28:05.010 --> 28:06.978
- I don't like
handing things off.

28:07.010 --> 28:10.377
- I'll save you the paperwork.

28:12.390 --> 28:14.881
- You just said the magic words.

28:21.100 --> 28:23.796
- Nice work, Maz.

28:23.830 --> 28:25.718
- Now we just gotta hope
that Pryce doesn't see

28:25.770 --> 28:27.931
the red recording light.
- You and I had a deal.

28:27.970 --> 28:32.339
You do as I say, lay low,
and I help you out.

28:32.370 --> 28:34.406
- I'm still waiting for
the "help" part to kick in.

28:34.440 --> 28:36.829
- What were you thinking,
lighting up in front of him?

28:36.880 --> 28:39.348
- How was I supposed to know
the guy was under

28:39.380 --> 28:42.178
- Keep it together, Jay.

28:44.390 --> 28:46.210
- I found out a friend
of mine died.

28:46.250 --> 28:49.356
Teddy Borges.

28:49.390 --> 28:52.359
He was shot twice in the head.

28:52.390 --> 28:55.359
I c-couldn't help
but wonder if he was...

28:55.400 --> 28:58.221
- W-working for you, too.

28:58.270 --> 29:01.967
Why is that?

29:02.000 --> 29:04.400
- My friend is dead.

29:04.440 --> 29:07.830
And I get the feeling you
wouldn't care if the same
thing happened to me.

29:07.880 --> 29:10.178
- No, we got nothing.

29:10.210 --> 29:12.405
Pryce has to actually
incriminate himself.

29:22.320 --> 29:25.380
- I am so close with Tyrell.
- He's gonna see the red
recording light.

29:25.430 --> 29:27.853
- Just one deal and he's ours.

29:27.900 --> 29:30.198
And you're the man who can
make that deal happen.

29:30.230 --> 29:32.790
- No, Jay's blocking him.

29:32.830 --> 29:34.866
- How'd you know Teddy
was shot twice in the head?

29:34.900 --> 29:38.028
How'd you know that?
- I spoke to his cousin.

29:38.070 --> 29:40.004
She told me.

29:40.040 --> 29:42.929
Look, you said the meeting in
the karaoke bar was my last,

29:42.980 --> 29:45.301
just like you said
the meeting before

29:45.350 --> 29:47.341
was the last and
the one before that.

29:47.380 --> 29:50.315
- Atta boy, Jay, you got this.
- Just one last deal.

29:50.350 --> 29:53.148
This one last thing and that's
it. It's the big one. It's the
one you've been working for.

29:55.260 --> 29:57.455
- Um...
- I thought it was the bathroom.

29:57.490 --> 30:00.288
- Nolan, just hear me out
for a second, OK?

30:03.260 --> 30:05.364
- Pryce is running
C.I.s off the books.

30:07.170 --> 30:10.901
- Look, we have a rogue cop on
our hands and we're right on
the verge of getting some--

30:10.940 --> 30:12.828
- No, whatever you think
you had would never stick,

30:12.870 --> 30:15.304
'cause you've got civilians
in the interview room.

30:15.340 --> 30:17.376
- Uh, Pryce is leaving with Jay.
- Come on, Maz.

30:17.410 --> 30:19.605
You know better than that.
You're killing me.

30:19.650 --> 30:22.312
- We're trying to stop that cop
from getting another kid killed!

30:22.350 --> 30:25.444
Who
deputized any of you to do that?

30:25.490 --> 30:28.311
You realize this right here is
enough to torch your promotion?

30:28.360 --> 30:30.419
- So be it.

30:33.090 --> 30:36.093
- We've breached protocol,
but Jay's in real danger, OK?

30:36.130 --> 30:38.098
Pryce is gunning so hard
for Tyrell that he's lost

30:38.130 --> 30:40.121
complete perspective of this--
- You don't get to tell me

30:40.170 --> 30:42.536
how to conduct police business.
- I'm sorry, but one young C.I.

30:42.570 --> 30:45.232
has already lost his life.
- Nolan, it was my decision.

30:45.270 --> 30:47.329
- Even if it wasn't,
it's going to land on you.

30:47.370 --> 30:50.271
Listen, I know you P.I.s
like to work the fringes,

30:50.310 --> 30:52.278
so maybe you thought you had
to go behind my back. But look,

30:52.310 --> 30:54.278
next time, overcome

30:54.320 --> 30:56.276
your natural impulses
and just come and talk to me.

30:56.320 --> 30:58.481
OK, look. I did some digging.

30:58.520 --> 31:02.957
Teddy Borges, found in a field
with two bullets in his head.

31:02.990 --> 31:06.380
Lisa Millegrew, 25.
She's a Forest Hill party girl

31:06.430 --> 31:09.228
whose Molly habit ended when her
body showed up at Cherry Beach.

31:09.260 --> 31:11.490
You see a pattern here?

31:11.530 --> 31:13.896
- Recreational users.

31:13.940 --> 31:15.669
- Both shot in the head, both
dumped in remote locations.

31:15.700 --> 31:18.430
- And both
confidential informants

31:18.470 --> 31:20.563
for a man who rides
his horses until they drop.

31:20.610 --> 31:23.977
I'll just wait out here.

31:24.010 --> 31:26.103
- Just get in here.
- OK.

31:26.150 --> 31:28.971
- Now, look. These two don't
show up on the CI. list,

31:29.020 --> 31:31.443
but I talked to a few
officers that I trust.

31:31.490 --> 31:33.515
Pryce was seen with
each of these victims...

31:33.550 --> 31:35.552
...on at least one OCCElSiOH.

31:38.030 --> 31:40.385
I got a line on Jay.

31:40.430 --> 31:43.126
Looks like he's driving
down Geary Avenue.

31:43.160 --> 31:45.162
I let him put some
apps on my phone.

31:45.200 --> 31:47.168
- Pryce must have had Jay set up
another buy with Tyrell.

31:47.200 --> 31:50.260
